class Solution(object):
    def missingInteger(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]:rtype: int
        """
        nums.sort()  # Sort the numbers to easily find the sequential prefix
        sum_sequential = 0
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            if i == 0 or nums[i] == nums[i-1] + 1:  # Check if current number continues the sequence
                sum_sequential += nums[i]
            else:
                break  # Stop at the first break of the sequence

        x = sum_sequential + 1  # Start looking for the missing integer just after the sum of the sequential prefix
        while x in nums:  # Ensure the missing integer is not in the list
            x += 1
        return x
